yllythad5267@yllythad.title: Wild, Foaming Crests
yllythad5267@yllythad.description:
The water rises and falls with such force that it seems the world must
be shaking on its foundations.  The water splashes and crashes against
itself, foam and froth all over the surface of the sea.

yllythad5261@yllythad.title: A Swift Wind
yllythad5261@yllythad.description:
A solid wind blows up from the east, carrying with it the tang and
fresh scent of the sea and all it's creatures.  There are little to no
clouds anywhere in the sky, the world seeming limitless from this
perspective.

yllythad5132@yllythad.title: East of the Jetty
yllythad5132@yllythad.description:
A long jetty made of jumbled rock pokes out into the sea, a lighthouse
perched at its end.  Fisherman sit along the sides of the jetty,
hoping to catch a little luck and maybe some dinner along with it.  
There does not appear any way to get west onto the jetty's walkway
from the sea.

yllythad5186@yllythad.title: A Swift Wind
yllythad5186@yllythad.description:
A good, steady wind blows from the east, making sea travel swift and
easy in this area.  The sea's currents move with the direction of the
winds, at least on the surface and help to lend direction to the
traveler.

yllythad5123@yllythad.title: A Drizzling Rain
yllythad5123@yllythad.description:
The rain falls in a steady drizzle that soaks to the bone, but does
not cause any harm.  The wind has all but died out, making the rain
all the final and somber.

yllythad5223@yllythad.title: A Drizzling Rain
yllythad5223@yllythad.description:
The rain falls in a steady drizzle that soaks to the bone, but does
not cause any harm.  The wind has all but died out, making the rain

yllythad5110@yllythad.title: A Strong Current
yllythad5110@yllythad.description:
This area of the sea is carried along by a strong undercurrent which
moves the water in its own direction, regardless of the wind or
weather topside.

yllythad5084@yllythad.title: Placid Waters
yllythad5084@yllythad.description:
The waters of the sea do not seem to move at all, not even with the
usual gentle up and down sway that all seas have.  Looking to the
horizon, the waters seem to go on forever.

yllythad5244@yllythad.title: In the Fog
yllythad5244@yllythad.description:
A thick fog has rolled in over the ocean's surface, obscuring what
lies ahead and making it almost impossible to see more than a few feet
ahead.  Things seems to have gotten just a little too quiet.

yllythad5288@yllythad.title: A Strong Current
yllythad5288@yllythad.description:

weather topside.

yllythad5180@yllythad.title: Calm Waters
yllythad5180@yllythad.description:

The sky and the water match almost exactly, so blue the water and so
clear the sky.

yllythad5151@yllythad.title: Upon the Mighty Sea
yllythad5151@yllythad.description:
All around is the wide open expanse of the sea, its mighty presence so
strong, so overwhelming as to be staggering.  From horizon to horizon,
only blue sky and a deeper blue can be seen.

yllythad5105@yllythad.title: At the Shoreline
yllythad5105@yllythad.description:
The sea has turned to calm that is almost unsettling.  Any sailor
would bow their head and say a quick prayer to the Sea God at this
time to pray for a wind of some sort.  Looking in all directions, the
sea is still and quiet.  A rocky shore is to the south, its boulder
riddled area too cluttered to be passed along.  A long jetty lies to
the east running north into the ocean, a tall lighthouse at its end.

yllythad5059@yllythad.title: Placid Waters
yllythad5059@yllythad.description:
There is no current and no winds.  The waters stand still and unmoving
here with no sign of change coming any time soon.  These are the types
of waters that sailors have nightmares about.

yllythad5021@yllythad.title: Among Fifteen Foot Waves
yllythad5021@yllythad.description:
A blinding storm has erupted across the seas, causing the water to
jump from casual swells to the fifteen foot walls which are now
completely surrounding this area.  Rain lashes down, stinging the sea
with its driving force.

sharp ends cutting into the water.  It does not appear safe to attempt
climbing those rocks to the lighthouse.
